The Kano State Government on Monday appointed the Emir of Bichi, Aminu Ado Bayero, as successor to deposed Emir Muhammadu Sanusi II. Aminu Ado Bayero was until his elevation the Emir of Bichi, one of the four newly created Emirates from the old Kano Emirate. The new Emir Ado Bayero, son of Sanusi II’s predecessor, Alhaji Ado Bayero, contested the stool against the deposed Emir in 2014. Details later… 